The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, March 22: The Torrent group today decided to amalgamate Torrent Power AEC, Torrent Power SEC and Torrent Power Generation into a single company, called Torrent Power Ltd. Under the arrangement, each shareholder of Torrent Power AEC will get 5.5 shares of Torrent Power Ltd for every share held and those of Torrent Power SEC will get 11.75 shares each.

 New Delhi, March 22: Heidelberg of Germany has forged a 50:50 joint venture with Indorama Cement. Heidelberg will pick up a controlling stake in Indorama?s 7.5-million-tonne cement plant near Mumbai.

 New Delhi, March 22: The Power Grid Corporation of India Ltd will form joint ventures with five more companies, including ONGC and Essar, to set up transmission lines in the country. 

 Mumbai, March 22: UTI Bank has raised Rs 500 crore tier-II capital through long-term debentures issued on a private placement basis. The bank will allot 5000 non-convertible debentures of Rs 10 lakh each. 

 Mumbai, March 22: Larsen amp; Toubro Ltd will raise $300 million (about Rs 1,350 crore) from overseas markets to fund its expansion and future acquisitions. The company?s board today approved raising the funds by issuing foreign currency convertible bonds.




